				\begin{document}$${\text{Decolorization efficiency }}\left( \%  \right)\, = \,\left( {{\text{A}}_{0} \, - \,{\text{A}}_{{\text{1}}} } \right)/{\text{A}}_{0} \, \times \,{\text{1}}00,$$\end{document}Decolorization efficiency%=A0-A1/A0×100,
where A0 and A1 are the absorption of MG before and after laccase treatment, respectively.
